title: Pa. boys and girls: Straka's goal lifts Conwell-Egan
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports Public League. Djavon Dupree scored two goals, and Lauren Irvine tallied one goal and an assist to lead Central over visiting Masterman, 7-1.
Penn-Jersey League. Talia Koltun-Fromm and Shira Perloff each scored two goals to lead Barrack Hebrew past visiting Girard College, 6-0. 
Ches-Mont. Chloe Smith netted two goals in Unionville's 2-0 home win over Coatesville. 
Nonleague. Sun Valley's Samantha Bowen headed in Olivia Lambert's cross with 2 minutes, 30 seconds remaining in regulation to knock off visiting Chichester, 3-2. 
Friends' Central edged visiting Hill School, 1-0 on Miranda Mastrocola's second-half goal. Boys' Soccer Liam Graves' blast from right behind the penalty area in double overtime gave visiting Franklin Towne Charter a 1-0 victory over host Philadelphia Academy Charter in Public League play.
Elsewhere in the Public League, Cristian Curtean's two goals led Washington to a 5-1 win at Southern. 
Nonleague. Asa Bell recorded a hat trick in Friends' Central's 6-2 victory at Academy of New Church. Field Hockey Jordyn Crossan's goal with 10 minutes left in regulation proved to be the winner as Archbishop Carroll knocked off Bonner-Prendergast, 1-0, in Catholic League play. 
Kimmy McGroary had five saves, including a penalty stroke. Girls' Tennis Central blanked visiting Lincoln, 5-0, in the Public League Class AAA semifinals.
Inter-Ac. Lexi Short and Kayla Neary each earned singles victories in Penn Charter's 4-2 home win over Agnes Irwin.
